g` is missing, and (2) no other artifact slots must be corrupted. Both require the implement skill to be wired to the artifact store so we can inspect the store's full state after execution. REAL-INFRA: No OS or network needed; an in-process fake store with pre-seeded artifacts is sufficient to catch corruption. LLM-DEP: A deterministic stub is enough to exercise the fallback path and check artifact store state. REJECTION-GATE: Unit rejected — store-state inspection for corruption detection is a cross-module concern. Agentic rejected — LLM quality is not what is being validated.","test_description":"Pre-seed an in-memory artifact store with a sentinel value in an unrelated artifact slot (e.g., `deep_dive_notes`). Leave `grounding` absent. Run the implement skill with a stubbed LLM. Assert (a) the `plan` artifact is written and parses as a valid plan structure, (b) no exception is raised, and (c) the pre-seeded `deep_dive_notes` artifact is unchanged after the run.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.07,"Workflow":0.05}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9906,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9906},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e313d525-01f4-4aa0-8222-d1e3a1a66995","uuid":"bd1a03db-2d64-461b-ac50-696ce83bd845"}
